-- China Everbright names 10 banks for HK float: IFR
-- 
-- Sat Mar 12, 2011 9:28pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/13/us-chinaeverbright-ipo-idUSTRE72C0AM20110313

 

 HONG KONG  (Reuters) - China Everbright Bank ( 601818.SS ) has mandated 10 banks for its planned about $6 billion Hong Kong listing, IFR reported late on Saturday. 

 The underwriters for the offer are: Bank of America Merrill Lynch ( BAC.N ), BOC International ( 3988.HK ), BNP Paribas ( BNPP.PA ), CICC, China Everbright Securities, Goldman Sachs ( GS.N ), Guotai Junan Securities, JP Morgan ( JPM.N ), Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) and UBS ( UBSN.VX ), IFR, a Thomson Reuters publication said. The lender aims to wrap up the deal by end July, it said. Last month, the Shanghai-listed mid-sized Chinese bank said it plans to issue up to 12 billion Hong Kong-listed shares, including an over allotment option, to boost its capital adequacy ratio. (Reporting by Jing Song and Fiona Lau; Editing by  Ron Popeski )